# Docker Daily-Life CLI Cheat Sheet

## PAGE 1 – COMMAND QUICK REFERENCE

### 1. Pull an Image
```
docker pull ubuntu
docker pull nginx:latest
```

### 2. Run a Container
```
docker run ubuntu
docker run -d nginx
docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
docker run -d -v myvol:/data nginx
```

### 3. Start / Stop / Restart
```
docker start <container-id>
docker stop <container-id>
docker restart <container-id>
```

### 4. Delete Containers & Images
```
docker rm <container-id>
docker rm -f <container-id>
docker rmi nginx
docker rmi nginx:latest
```

### 5. Inspect
```
docker inspect <container-id>
docker inspect <image-id>
```

### 6. Logs
```
docker logs <container-id>
docker logs -f <container-id>
```

### 7. Exec
```
docker exec -it <container-id> bash
docker exec -it <container-id> sh
```

### 8. Networks
```
docker network ls
docker network inspect <network-name>
```

### 9. Volumes
```
docker volume create myvol
docker volume ls
docker volume inspect myvol
```

## PAGE 2 – EXAMPLE PROJECT WORKFLOWS

### Scenario A – Start a Web Server
```
docker run -d -p 8080:80 --name web nginx
docker logs web
docker stop web
docker rm web
```

### Scenario B – Debug Container
```
docker exec -it web bash
exit
```

### Scenario C – Persistent Volume
```
docker volume create dbdata
docker run -d -v dbdata:/var/lib/mysql --name mydb mysql:latest
```

### Scenario D – Clean Up All
```
docker stop $(docker ps -aq)
docker rm $(docker ps -aq)
docker rmi $(docker images -q)
docker volume rm $(docker volume ls -q)
```

### Scenario E – Inspect Networking
```
docker network ls
docker inspect web
```
